verbose_text: Moreover, several MtSWEET genes, such as MtSWEET1b, MtSWEET3c, MtSWEET11, MtSWEET12, and MtSWEET15c, were preferentially expressed during nodule development (XREF_FIG B), indicating their roles in the sugar efflux that eventually feeds the symbionts [XREF_BIBR].
